<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-02-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Fox</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-02-25"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 25, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your interesting letter of
                            this date, giving an account of the manner in which you have executed
                            the instructions of this department with reference to the presentation
                            to the Emperor of Russia of the resolution of Congress congratulating
                            him upon his escape from an attempted assassination. In reply, I have to
                            inform you that your proceedings upon the occasion referred to are
                            entirely approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p> G. V. Fox, Esq.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>